        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            


<p><placeName>Durham Hall</placeName> <date when="1811-10-08">October 8th 1811</date></p>
<p>Dr Sir</p>

<p>I have finally concluded to let you have the <placeName>mill </placeName>for 13,000&#8212;
Your offer was twelve and I will split the difference&#8212; I hope we
shall be able to bargain as I am desireous to Sell&#8212; hope shall soon
have the pleasure of seeing you at the <placeName>Mines </placeName>a little company would
be very acceptable at this time for I never saw this place half so
dismal as it appears now&#8212; The waggons will hawl out a load of
plank for <persName>Evins </persName>and return immediately to hawl for you as long as
you wish&#8212;</p>

<p>If you have any Salt come out from the <placeName>village </placeName>yet please send
out some.</p>

<p><persName>Stephen F. Austin</persName></p>

<p><persName>Mr James Bryan</persName></p>

<p>[Addressed:] <persName>Mr James Bryan</persName> <placeName>Hazle Run</placeName></p>

 

        </div1>
